9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 707, L.D. 1816, “An Act to Establish a
10 Statewide Sexual Assault Forensic Examination Kit Tracking System and Conduct an
11 Inventory of Existing Forensic Examination Kits in the Possession of Law Enforcement”
12 Amend the bill by inserting after the title and before the emergency preamble the
13 following:
14 'Mandate preamble. This measure requires one or more local units of government
15 to expand or modify activities so as to necessitate additional expenditures from local
16 revenues but does not provide funding for at least 90% of those expenditures. Pursuant to
17 the Constitution of Maine, Article IX, Section 21, 2/3 of all of the members elected to each
18 House have determined it necessary to enact this measure; and'
19 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and before the
20 emergency clause and inserting the following:
21 'Sec. 1. 24 MRSA §2986, sub-§3, as amended by PL 2025, c. 109, §3, is further
22 amended to read:
23 3. Completed kit. If the victim has not reported the alleged offense to a law
24 enforcement agency when the examination is complete, the hospital or health care
25 practitioner shall then notify the nearest law enforcement agency, which shall transport and
26 store the completed forensic examination kit for 8 20 years. The completed kit may be
27 identified only by the tracking number. If during that storage period a victim decides to
28 report the alleged offense to a law enforcement agency, the victim may contact the hospital
29 or health care practitioner to determine the tracking number. The hospital or health care
30 practitioner shall provide the victim with the tracking number on the forensic examination
31 kit and shall inform the victim which law enforcement agency is storing the kit.
32 If the victim reports the alleged offense to a law enforcement agency by the time the
33 examination is complete, the investigating agency shall retain custody of the forensic
34 examination kit.
