5 SUMMARY
66 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, adds a mandate
77 preamble and makes technical changes to the provisions of the bill requiring the
88 Department of Public Safety to maintain a tracking system for all completed forensic
99 examination kits to add clarity, including by clarifying that a completed forensic
1100 examination kit may be processed by either the Maine State Police Crime Laboratory
1111 located in Augusta or another accredited laboratory that provides forensic services to law
1122 enforcement agencies for the purpose of analyzing forensic examination kits. The
1133 amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
